# Important Definitions

## Registers

The fastest memory located inside the CPU that stores the data currently being processed.

---

## Cache Memory

Memory that stores frequently used data to reduce CPU access time.

---

## RAM

Temporary memory used to store running programs and data.

---

## ROM

Permanent memory used to store firmware.

---

## Stack Memory

Memory used to store method calls, local variables, and reference variables.

---

## Heap Memory

Memory used to store objects and arrays.

---

# Common Interview Mistakes

❌ Objects are stored in Stack.

✅ Objects are stored in Heap.

---

❌ Reference variables are stored in Heap.

✅ Reference variables are stored in Stack.

---

❌ RAM stores files permanently.

✅ RAM stores data temporarily while programs are running.

---

❌ ROM stores user files.

✅ ROM stores firmware such as BIOS/UEFI.

